What you need to know:

Most damages are attributed to poor post-harvest practices, informal marketing system and unfavourable physical environmental.Most farmers store their maize using archaic methods that expose them to substantial pest damage and growth of mould, loss of dry matter and reduced grain quality.Shelling of maize can be done by hand or using a mechanical sheller, depending on the volumes.Treatment of grains is done with insecticidal dusts at the rate of 50g per 90kg bag. The products are readily available in agrovet shops.